text: Masherbrum is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. It was also once known as K1. It is the 22nd highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top of Masherbrum were George Irving Bell and Willi Unsoeld, in 1960. ==References== Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
title: Masherbrum
